Mom and newborn baby [Courtesy]  Turkana County has received assorted medical supplies from Amref Health Africa to boost provision of medical services in remote areas.  Project Officer Galgalo Golicha said the donations included 10 delivery beds, 10 major delivery sets, 720 pieces of maternity pads, 300 mosquito nets, 200 mama kits, four ward screens and examination couches.  County Health Executive Jane Ajele said the supplies will boost operations of maternity units in rural health facilities.     Amref rolls out civic education campaigns to boost vaccines uptake  Amref rolls out civic education campaigns to boost vaccines uptake  Why youth are avoiding Covid-19 jab  Delegates assess impact of Covid-19 on Universal Health Coverage  AMREF releases results on the youth and COVID-19  AMREF offers services on charity basis, Standard Group CEO Orlando Lyomu attended  AMREF unveils road map for sustainable growth in health sectors By Yvonne Chepkwony | 6 hours ago By Ndiritu Muriithi | 6 hours ago By Winfrey Owino | 7 hours ago By Robert Kiplagat  | 1 day ago